programming.response:
Functions are like recipes - instructions you can reuse!

Example: Calculating mobile data costs in Sierra Leone:

```javascript
function calculateDataCost(gigabytes) {
  const pricePerGB = 50000; // Le per GB
  return gigabytes * pricePerGB;
}

console.log(calculateDataCost(5)); // 250000 Le
```

Functions help avoid repeating code. Want more examples?

Loops repeat actions - like doing something over and over!

